# 32k-context variant of qwen3-coder (30B MoE) for Open Code on Mac Mini M4 Pro 24GB.
#
# Why: Open Code talks to Ollama via the OpenAI-compatible (/v1) endpoint, which
# ignores options.num_ctx — so the base model loads at Ollama's 4096 default inside
# Open Code despite the architecture supporting 256k. Baking num_ctx in guarantees the
# real window is always active. Without this, the M4's flagship model effectively sees
# only ~3,000 words — less than ministral-3:8b-32k.
#
# Tool use: confirmed (coding-optimized MoE, ~3B active params per token).
#
# Build:  ollama create qwen3-coder:30b-32k -f modelfiles/qwen3-coder-30b-32k.Modelfile

FROM qwen3-coder:30b
PARAMETER num_ctx 32768
